comments: Irving (BKN) and Beasley (UTA) engage and disengage with one another along the perimeter.

O'Neale (BKN) is moving alongside Clarkson (UTA) and marginal contact occurs with Clarkson's left side at the end of the drive. Curry (BKN) then makes clean fingertip contact with the ball as Clarkson elevates to pass.
Kessler (UTA) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Conley (UTA) briefly has his arm around Simmons' (BKN) midsection before correcting.

Simmons (BKN) is firming up over his left foot and absorbs the contact with Conley (UTA) to his upper half before marginal lower body contact occurs thereafter. Simmons re-establishes slightly as he is absorbing the initial contact and further marginal contact occurs as Conley goes over the pick.
Markkanen (UTA) and O'Neale (BKN) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs as the pick expires.
Markkanen (UTA) brings his left arm outward and marginal contact occurs with O'Neale's (BKN) left arm as O'Neale defends the pass.
O'Neale (BKN) slightly extends forward prior to marginal body contact occurring with Markkanen (UTA) as Markkanen drives inside the perimeter.
O'Neale (BKN) is bracing for the impending contact with Markkanen (UTA) and absorbs it as it occurs when Markkanen backs O'Neale down in the post.
O'Neale (BKN) initiates contact across Markkanen's (UTA) left wrist, affecting Markkanen's SQBR and causing him to lose control of the ball.
Simmons (BKN) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Markkanen (UTA) prior to any incidental arm contact occurring during the loose ball sequence.
O'Neale's (BKN) legs are extended forward and he initiates contact with Markkanen's (UTA) legs prior to and after the release of his shot attempt, causing Markkanen to fall.
Clarkson (UTA) engages and disengages with O'Neale (BKN) during the inbound.
Correctly called 24 second violation on Utah.
Conley (UTA) is moving alongside Irving's (BKN) path and marginal body contact occurs prior to Irving slowing his momentum at the end of the drive.
Markkanen (UTA) is retreating alongside Irving's (BKN) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs as they come together.
Claxton (BKN) briefly has his arms around Markkanen's (UTA) upper half before correcting.
Harris (BKN) initiates leg-to-leg contact with Sexton (UTA) and causes Sexton to become dislodged after his gather.
Sexton (UTA) and Curry (BKN) come together at the same spot in the lane and incidental body contact occurs during the loose ball sequence.
Clarkson (UTA) commits a take foul on Harris (BKN).
Sexton (UTA) commits a take foul on Irving (BKN).
Conley (UTA) commits a take foul on Irving (BKN).
Claxton (BKN) engages and disengages with Markkanen (UTA) along the perimeter.
Curry (BKN) and Claxton (BKN) legally contest Conley's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Markkanen (UTA) and Simmons (BKN) each make clean contact with the ball prior to any incidental arm contact occurring during the rebound.
